Package dataRepresentationsExtensions.logs

Class Logged

java.lang.Object
dataRepresentationsExtensions.logs.Logged
public class Logged extends Object
Manages creation and preparation of variables to be aggregated according to used abstraction level - instantiates functionality to aggregate variables from different code constructs to prepare logging command (variable dependencies if collected from final products)
Author:
Jakub Perdek

      public Logged(String variabilityPointIdentifier, String loggerId)
      Instantiates functionality to aggregate variables from different code constructs to prepare logging command (variable dependencies if collected from final products)
      Parameters:
      variabilityPointIdentifier - - string identification of variation point representation
      loggerId - - the identifier of particular logger - information about operation level under code is (should be) included during its generation

    • Logged

      public Logged(DataRepresentationsConfiguration dataRepresentationsConfiguration, String variabilityPointIdentifier, String loggerId, String className, String additionalObjectString)
      Instantiates functionality to aggregate variables from different code constructs to prepare logging command (variable dependencies if collected from final products)
      Parameters:
      dataRepresentationsConfiguration - - the configuration with logging detail and optionally also target variables
      variabilityPointIdentifier - - string identification of variation point representation
      loggerId - - the identifier of particular logger - information about operation level under code is (should be) included during its generation
      className - - the name of processed class if any (optional)
      additionalObjectString - - additional information used to identify variation point - such as function arguments,...

    • Logged

      public Logged(String variabilityPointIdentifier, String loggerId, String className, String additionalObjectString, boolean notLogObjects, boolean notLogFunctions)
      Instantiates functionality to aggregate variables from different code constructs to prepare logging command (variable dependencies if collected from final products)
      Parameters:
      variabilityPointIdentifier - - string identification of variation point representation
      loggerId - - the identifier of particular logger - information about operation level under code is (should be) included during its generation
      className - - the name of processed class if any (optional)
      additionalObjectString - - additional information used to identify variation point - such as function arguments,...
      notLogObjects - - sets to not log objects - objects will not be logged if true otherwise they will
      notLogFunctions - - sets to not log any functions - any function will not be logged if true otherwise they will
